  "text": "Transformer experiments. We use the Fairseq implementation for 12-layer transformer models and inherit the key hyperparameters from the Fairseq repository. [CITATION_1] We use 2× longer learning rate linear warmup steps than in the original code repository across experiments because we observe 2× linear warmup steps can produce higher BLEU scores for both the synchronous and asynchronous runs. For both the IWSLT14 and WMT17 German to English dataset, we use beam width 5 to evaluate the BLEU score. We present the other hyperparameters in Table 7 for reproducibility.",
